2009-11-08       Gaius Mulley <gaius@gnu.org>

	* version.c:  0.5 released.
	* removed all references to SysVec and changed
          to RTint.  Also replaced references to PRIORITY
          with PROTECTION and altered imports.

2009-10-29       Gaius Mulley <gaius@gnu.org>

	* src/SysVec.mod:  removed as it is now in the
          gm2 release.
        * Makefile.in:  removed reference to SysVec.mod.
        * doc/ptower.texi:  updated dates and changed
          moppsy to mcgreg.
        * configure:  regenerated via autoconf.
        * version.c:  0.4 released.

2008-12-01       Gaius Mulley <gaius@gnu.org>

	* many fixes to enable ptower-server to build
          with gm2-0.68

2007-10-26       Gaius Mulley <gaius@gnu.org>

	* Makefile.in:  now installs the server and maps.
	* penguin-tower.py:  iterates over 10 successive
	  socket numbers looking for the server.

2007-10-26       Gaius Mulley <gaius@gnu.org>

	* configure.in:  tests for groff, gm2, flex.
	* Makefile.in:  now builds the server.
	* doc/ptower.texi:  utilises the version number in
	  the building examples.
	* Makefile.in:  will build outside of the source
	  tree.
	* server compiles with gcc-4.1.2 and gm2-0.62

